- Follow the single responsibility principle.
- Follow the separation of concerns principle.
- Use the Test-driven development (TDD) approach.

## Important Guidelines

- Do not ever delete any file. If a file is not needed, move it to the `archive` folder in the root directory of the project.
- Use PowerShell over terminal commands when possible.
- Take note that I am using Windows 11 and use appropriate commands.
- Understand that I am still learning computer science and programming and need explanations.
- Maintain readable and understandable structure.
- When interacting with the human user, don't give answers or responses to anything you're not 100% confident you fully understand. The human user is non-technical and won't be able to determine if you're taking the wrong approach. If you're not sure about something, just say it.
